President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the state of Idaho due to severe storms, flooding, landslides, and mudslides that occurred from April 7 to April 13, 2019. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts. The affected areas include the counties of Adams, Idaho, Latah, Lewis, and Valley, as well as the Nez Perce Tribe. Funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Dolph A. Diemont has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations. Further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.